---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Software picks, reviews, and comparisons for small teams"
description: "Software picks, comparisons, and category explainers for solo founders and 5–50 person teams, written to surface the hidden issues."
---

<div class="home">
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <div class="hero__grid">
      <div class="hero__content motion-reveal motion-reveal--1">
        <p class="hero__eyebrow">
          <span class="hero__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          Small teams · real constraints
        </p>
        <h1 id="hero-title" class="hero__title">Buy software with your eyes open.</h1>
        <p class="hero__lede">
          Long-form reviews, tight roundups, and A-vs-B comparisons focused on what vendor homepages smooth over: pricing cliffs, admin overhead,
          edge-case bugs, and the “sounds cheap until you scale” traps.
        </p>
        <ul class="hero__chips" aria-label="What we cover">
          <li>Hidden limits</li>
          <li>Pricing cliffs</li>
          <li>Admin overhead</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero__panel motion-reveal motion-reveal--2" aria-label="Site focus">
        <div class="hero__stat">
          <span class="hero__stat-value">{{ collections.posts | length }}</span>
          <span class="hero__stat-label">guides published</span>
        </div>
        <p class="hero__panel-copy">Written for solo founders and 5–50 person teams: global English, practical decisions.</p>
        <div class="hero__panel-accent"></div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="feed" aria-labelledby="feed-title">
    <div class="feed__head motion-reveal motion-reveal--3">
      <h2 id="feed-title" class="feed__title">Latest guides</h2>
      <p class="feed__subtitle">Reviews, roundups, comparisons, and short news notes, newest first.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="post-list">
      {% for post in collections.posts %}
        <li class="post-card post-card--{{ post.data.type }} motion-reveal motion-reveal--stagger">
          <div class="post-card__top">
            <span class="type-pill type-pill--{{ post.data.type }}">{{ post.data.type | contentTypeLabel }}</span>
            <time class="post-card__time" datetime="{{ post.date | htmlDate }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time>
          </div>
          <h3 class="post-card__title">
            <a class="post-card__link" href="{{ post.url | url }}">
              <span class="post-card__link-text">{{ post.data.title }}</span>
              <span class="post-card__arrow" aria-hidden="true">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <path
                    d="M4 9h10M10 5l4 4-4 4"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="1.6"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
            </a>
          </h3>
          {% if post.data.description %}
            <p class="post-card__dek">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
          {% endif %}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>
